BASH Programming - Introduction HOW-TO

Translated by LinuxReview Team

How to Generate PDF document:
This document was written with xepersian package, so you need to have xelatex
installed on your system before running the make command. The fonts that were
used for writing this document are Linux Libertine, XB Niloofar, Yas and
Courier 10 Pitch. Obviously, These fonts should also be installed on you 
system.
If all goes well, after running the make command, you should see a file 
named bash-prog-intro-howto.pdf in source directory, which is the PDF output 
of this document. 